She only felt the burning as she yelped.

Stumbling she twisted around & glared at Tyrael. Fluid dripped from the 
laceration that the talons caused upon the side of her right cheek, looked almost 
like blood, but it wasn't. 

She glared at Tyrael as Hydras fought back. She panted as she tried to stay 
on her feet. 

"Alpha Trion... is.. an old.. Autobot.. Fool! He .. governs my.. existance... 
as much as Unicron .. could destroy... the ... Matrix." She knew Alpha Trion 
had a hold in her resurrection & refusal to restore her old form. At least... 
not yet. But... she would never let Alpha Trion tell her what to do. He was 
not her Mentor.... Gamma was. 

"NO .. Decepticon.. is a.. Slave!" she growled.

--part1_43.1f817e18.2c3f8aca_boundary
